article.description: D.J. Balentine passed the 2,000-point career mark on Thursday night while scoring a game-high 26 and Evansville beat Norfolk State 84-70.
article.headline: Balentine reaches 2,000, Evansville beats Norfolk St. 84-70
article.linkText: Balentine reaches 2,000, Evansville beats Norfolk St. 84-70
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. -- D.J. Balentine passed the 2,000-point career mark on Thursday night while scoring a game-high 26 and Evansville beat Norfolk State 84-70. Evansville (9-2) took the lead for good early in the second after a first half where Norfolk State (4-7) had the largest lead at 37-31 with 1:28 left. The Purple Aces closed the half with five straight points from there and opened the second with the next seven to lead 43-37. Balentine's 2,000th point came on the second of two free throws with 9:22 left, near the start of a 15-6 run that he also capped with free throws at 70-56. Balentine finished the game with 2,006 career points, joining Colt Ryan, Larry Humes and Marcus Wilson as the fourth member of Evansville's 2,000-point club. Jaylon Brown added 17 points and Egidijus Mockeviciu 14, plus 10 boards, for the Aces. Jeff Short led Norfolk State with 22 points.
